      "text": "## Gaussian integral\n\nIn ```1809```, mathematician *Karl Friedrich Gauss* proved that the following holds:\n$$ \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}e^{-ax^2} \\text{d}x = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}} $$\nThis is a **very interesting** mathematical result. It can be proven using a polar coordinate substitution."
